				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Actually the damage delay ratio on the Razing Sword is 25/40, not 20/40.  So yes the Razing Sword has a much better damage delay ratio than the Claymore.  If you take away the stat bonuses this weapon has, then basically this weapon is just a bit better than a GZ, and far inferior to a weapon like a Mithril Two-Handed Sword.  However Paladins do not have to fret, the mob that drops this sword also drops the Darkmetal Holy Water Sprinkler which is 1h blunt, 16/29 and +4 wis. (yeah, you can't dual wield em, but so what put a shield in the other hand a bash :)
